<item>
            <title>[OAK-2429] MissingIndexProviderStrategy too eager to set the reindex flag</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2429</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Following &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2203&quot; title=&quot;Full reindexing is triggered when the IndexEditor is missing&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OAK-2203&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OAK-2203&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the MissingIndexProviderStrategy will set the reindex flag is a provider is missing. What is doesn&apos;t take into account is if the reindex flag is already set to &apos;true&apos;. If this is the case, it should skip setting it again.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve ran into this while working on the cold standby and some &apos;disabled&apos; type indexes were always getting updated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
